%U A396017 1079193820,2884163147,7717665942,20607086269,55082558748,146961256062,392462843328,1046372618275
%N A396017 Number of primitive undirected self-avoiding paths of length n in the square lattice; i.e., A037245 with nonprimitive paths excluded.
%C A396017 Here a primitive path is one which is not a repetition of a smaller path or congruent to a smaller path, e.g. the 3 cases for n = 4 which are counted in A037245 and not counted here (denoted here as positive direction steps in XY coordinates) are: path XYXY, which is a repetition of smaller primitive path XY, path XXYY, which is congruent to smaller primitive path XY, and path XXXX, which is both a repetition of and congruent to smaller primitive path X.
%F A396017 a(p) = A037245(p) - 1 for prime p.
%Y A396017 Cf. A037245.
%K A396017 nonn,walk
%O A396017 1,3
%A A396017 _Charles L. Hohn_, May 14 2026
